fr.pyvain.websight.websight.PersonalDataGraph

Class InputGraph

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.pyvain.websight.websight.PersonalDataGraph.InputGraph

  • public final class InputGraph
extends java.lang.Object

    This class represents a general undirected graph. Such a graph can be built from a json encoded graph received from the server.

    • Constructor Detail

      • InputGraph

        public InputGraph(java.util.List<Vertex> vertices,
                  java.util.List<Edge> edges)
           throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Initializes a new input graph containing specified vertices and edges. Merges vertices which have the same ends. Adds neighbours to the vertices according to the edges. All the ends of the specified edges must be among specified vertices. The specified vertices must not already have neighbours. The specified vertices must have consecutive, increasing ids starting from 0.
        Parameters:
        vertices - Vertices of the graph
        edges - Edges of the graph
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if one of the 3 requirements above is not met.

      • InputGraph

        public InputGraph(java.lang.String graph)
           throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Initializes a new graph from a json encoded graph received from the server.
        Parameters:
        graph - A graph encoded with the following JSON format { "urls": ["url1", ..., "urlM"], "vertices": **JSON spec of the vertices, see parseVertices**, "edges": **JSON spec of the edges, see parseEdges**, }
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if graph is not valid
        See Also:
        parseVertices(JSONArray, JSONArray), parseEdges(JSONArray, JSONArray, java.util.List<fr.pyvain.websight.websight.PersonalDataGraph.Vertex>)

      • randomInputGraph

        public static InputGraph randomInputGraph(int nbVertices,
                                          int nbEdges)
                                   throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Random data graph generator. Builds a data graph which has the specified number of vertices and edges, containing no urls.
        Parameters:
        nbVertices - number of vertices wanted
        nbEdges - number of edges wanted
        Returns:
        a random data graph which has the specified number of vertices and edges
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the number of edges is to high for the number of vertices (i.e. E > V*(V-1)/2)
